---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Header from '../components/Header.astro'
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Gophy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Gophy. Learn how we handle your data."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="pt-24 pb-16 bg-background text-foreground">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-8">Last updated: February 2026</p>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <section class="card p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            Gophy ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy.
            This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information
            when you use our native macOS application and related services.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="card p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">2. Local-First Processing</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            Gophy processes all data locally on your Mac using on-device AI models.
            No audio or meeting data is sent to external servers unless you explicitly
            configure a cloud AI provider. Transcription, suggestions, and document
            analysis all happen entirely on your device.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="card p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">3. Information We Collect</h2>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-foreground mt-4 mb-2">3.1 App Settings</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
            Your application preferences and configuration are stored locally on your device.
            We do not transmit or store your settings on any remote server.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-foreground mt-4 mb-2">3.2 Google Calendar Integration</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
            If you choose to connect Google Calendar, we store OAuth tokens and calendar
            sync tokens locally on your device to fetch upcoming meeting details. We access
            only calendar event metadata (title, time, attendees) needed for meeting
            preparation. You can disconnect Google Calendar at any time from the app settings.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-foreground mt-4 mb-2">3.3 Cloud AI Providers</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
            If you configure a cloud AI provider (e.g., OpenAI, Anthropic), data you choose
            to send to those services is governed by their respective privacy policies.
            Gophy stores your API keys locally and never transmits them to our servers.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-foreground mt-4 mb-2">3.4 Crash Reports</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            With your consent, we may collect anonymized crash reports to improve app stability.
            These reports do not contain meeting content, audio data, or personal information.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="card p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">4. Audio Data</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            During active meetings, audio is captured and processed entirely on your device
            using local AI models. <strong class="text-foreground">Audio is never sent to our servers
            and is never stored persistently.</strong> It is processed transiently in memory and
            discarded immediately after generating transcriptions and suggestions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="card p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">5. Data Security</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            Because Gophy operates locally on your device, your data benefits from your
            Mac's built-in security features including FileVault encryption, Gatekeeper,
            and the App Sandbox. API keys and OAuth tokens are stored securely in the
            macOS Keychain.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="card p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">6. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
            Gophy may interact with the following third-party services only when you
            explicitly configure them:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-muted-foreground space-y-2">
            <li><strong class="text-foreground">Google Calendar</strong> - Calendar sync for meeting preparation (OAuth)</li>
            <li><strong class="text-foreground">Cloud AI Providers</strong> - Optional cloud-based AI processing (your API keys, your choice)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="card p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">7. Your Rights</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-4">
            You have the right to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-muted-foreground space-y-2">
            <li>Access all your data directly on your device</li>
            <li>Delete all app data by removing the application</li>
            <li>Disconnect any third-party integrations at any time</li>
            <li>Opt out of crash reporting</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="card p-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground mb-4">8. Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground">
            If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
            <a href="mailto:privacy@gophy.ai" class="text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">
              privacy@gophy.ai
            </a>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
